devdoc.details: This contract shows how to work with boolean values in Solidity

areBothTrue().details: Function to check if both boolean values are true

returns._0: Returns true only if both value and val2 are true

check(uint256).details: Function to check if input value is greater than 100

params.a: The uint256 value to check against 100

returns._0: Returns true if a > 100, false otherwise

isEitherTrue().details: Function to check if at least one boolean value is true

returns._0: Returns true if either value or val2 is true

toggleValue().details: Function to toggle the value between true and false
